snippet.textDisplay: Lamar Jackson truly is changing the role of a quarterback. Along with his amazing athletic skills, he's also got smart and strong mental capabilities. The reason this entire offense is so successful is because defenses can't adjust and don't have the experience in having a quarterback that can not only throw the ball extremely well, but also in the blink of an eye can turn into a dangerous running back. Add to that his agile athletic ability to escape/bounce around in the pocket and the IQ to know when he should throw or keep and you've got the most dangerous quarterback this game has ever seen. And it's not like he's a tough running back, he's an extremely smart and agile one. He can run like Emmit Smith, but just before he gets hit he dives down or steps out. If you cover your receivers too tight and leave 10 yards open, Lamar has the ability to keep and take that 10 yards. If you try to cover the 10 yards in anticipation of Lamar keeping, you give a little extra space to the receiver that Lamar knows he can take advantage of and throw. Lamar has the ability to misdirect the defenses to create opportunities. And that hesitation in the defense gives Ingram and all the receivers the opportunity to get 1 or 2 steps ahead of their man. Quarterbacks have been protected and pampered for too long. That's how the game has been played forever. To finally see a quarterback that has the ability and courage to, in the blink of an eye, turn into a high IQ and high level threatening running back is amazing. We are watching the birth of a new era in football. The game will be forever changed. Coaches and scouts are going to be looking for that Tom Brady that can run like Saquon Barkley. Welcome to the LJ era.
